HEADWORD: Accouchement
<hw>Ac*couche"ment</hw> <pr>(#; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
fr. <ets>accoucher</ets> to be delivered of a child, to aid in delivery,
OF. <ets>acouchier</ets> orig. to lay down, put to bed, go to bed; L.
<ets>ad</ets> + <ets>collocare</ets> to lay, put, place. See
<er>Collate</er>.]</ety> <def>Delivery in childbed</def>⟦br⟧
